<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-02-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="234" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Wos y Gil</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-12"><hi rend="italic">February 12,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 5th instant, inclosing a memorandum of the
                            circumstances which led to the rupture of diplomatic relations between
                            the Dominican Republic and France.</p>
                        <p>The question has been made the subject of appropriate instructions to our
                            ambassador at Paris and chargé d’affaires near the Dominican
                            Republic.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>